summary: Just as everyone, I'm extremely excited about Eve's sexuality being a huge part of this season. But unlike some of you, I don't...
body:
Just as everyone, I’m extremely excited about Eve’s sexuality being a huge part of this season. But unlike some of you, I don’t think it has to be exactly about Eve having sex with Villanelle. PLEASE, DON’T GET ME WRONG. I would love to see this happening, but I truly want to see Eve being attracted to another woman first. Preferably, normal woman. I think it will be important to her - individually speaking - because she may be out there thinking she likes Villanelle for being a *murderer*, not because she is a *woman*, and this can really confuse her mind, you know? Like, “I am straight but I will make an exception for this psychopath because I have a fascination with psychopaths and that is the only reason, it‘s totally not because I like puss*”. Maybe, to some of you it doesn’t make any sense, but I went through something similar with my own sexuality and it was something extremely confusing to me. If it was confusing to me, can you imagine how confusing it would be to a woman who spent her whole life having sex with men?

Again, please, don’t get me wrong. I ship Villaneve, I love their relationship and I totally want to see them having sex, but I believe that before this can happen, Eve needs to explore and get comfortable with her own sexuality first.

title: Dueling lesbian “Fiona Shaw”s.
body:
FYI kiddos. There’s an article going around about “Fiona Shaw” that is conflating Fiona Shaw the Actress with Fiona Shaw the Author.

It’s understandable that some people would confuse the name and the fact they both date women - but this article is some kind of machine-bot trash that doesn’t even appear to written by a human being, or a least not anyone who’s English is their first language.

Here’s the original article about the AUTHOR Fiona Shaw coming out to her kids and revealing that her ex-husband is also gay. 

I can’t find any information about Fiona Shaw the ACTRESS having children or having ever been married to a man at all (I could be wrong.)  Be didligent people, check your sources ALWAYS CHECK YOUR SOURCES.
